    <subsection xml:id="subsec-Division-of-a-decimal-number-by-a-decimal-number">
        <title>Division of a decimal number by a decimal number</title>
        <p>
            To divide decimal numbers you:
            <ol marker="a)">
                <li>
                    <p>
                      Express the division as a fraction .Example <m>6.3 √∑ 0.7 </m> can be written as 
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <m>\frac{63}{10} \div \frac{7}{10}</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Convert division into multiplication that is instead of dividing, multiply the first fraction by the reciprocal of the second fraction i.e
                     </p>
                     <p>
                        <m>\frac{63}{10} \times \frac{10}{7}</m> = <m>\frac{63}{\cancel{10}} \times \frac{\cancel{10}}{7}</m>
                     </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Simplify the fraction : <m>\frac{63}{7}</m> = <m>9</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
