        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Erick had a sugarcane whose length was <m>6.24</m> m. He cut the sugarcane into equal pieces of <m>1.04</m> m. How many pieces did he get?
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    Equal pieces of sugarcane Erick got is given by:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>6.24 \text{ m } \div 1.04 \text{ m } = \frac{6.24}{1.04}</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Multiply both the numerator and the denomenator by <m>100</m> to eliminate the decimals. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\frac{6.24 \times 100}{1.04 \times 100} \amp = \frac{624}{104}</mrow>
                        <mrow> \amp </mrow>
                        <mrow> \amp = 6 </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                  Therefore,  Erick got <m>6</m> pieces of sugarcane.
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
